Step 1. Current Ratio  
• Total Current Assets = 9,221,098.50  
• Total Current Liabilities = 378,850.51  
• Current Ratio = 9,221,098.50 ÷ 378,850.51 ≈ 24.32

Step 2. Gross Profit Margin  
• Gross Profit = 1,622,011.03  
• Total Revenue = 2,637,011.03  
• Gross Profit Margin = (1,622,011.03 ÷ 2,637,011.03) × 100 ≈ 61.50%

Step 3. Debt to Asset Ratio  
• Total Liabilities (which in this case equals Total Current Liabilities) = 378,850.51  
• Total Assets = 14,214,117.02  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 378,850.51 ÷ 14,214,117.02 ≈ 0.03

Step 4. Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit = 835,266.51  
• Total Revenue = 2,637,011.03  
• Net Profit Margin = (835,266.51 ÷ 2,637,011.03) × 100 ≈ 31.67%

Step 5. Cash to Current Debt Ratio  
• Cash and Cash Equivalents (Ending Balance) = 6,885,735.26  
• Total Current Liabilities = 378,850.51  
• Cash to Current Debt Ratio = 6,885,735.26 ÷ 378,850.51 ≈ 18.18

Step 6. Free Cash Flow (FCF)  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –1,028,375.55  
• Purchase of Fixed Assets (Investing outflow) = 85,889.19  
• FCF = Operating Cash Flow – Capital Expenditures  
  = –1,028,375.55 – 85,889.19  
  ≈ –1,114,264.74

Step 7. Return on Assets (ROA)  
• ROA = (Net Profit ÷ Total Assets) × 100  
  = (835,266.51 ÷ 14,214,117.02) × 100  
  ≈ 5.88%

Now, putting it all together in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "24.32",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "61.50%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.03",
    "Net Profit Margin": "31.67%",
    "Cash to Current Debt Ratio": "18.18",
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-1114264.74",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "5.88%"
  }
}
